blocks.name: csbdif
blocks.content: Distribution of class substitution over difference of two classes. (Contributed by ML, 14-Jul-2020.)
blocks.origin:
thm csbdif(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  |- wceq(csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2)))
} = {
  pm2.61i(wceq(csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2))), wcel(c0, universe))
  vtoclg(hs0, c0, universe, wceq(csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2))), wceq(csb(s0, cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2))))
  eqeq12d(csb(s0, cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2)), csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2)), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, cdif(c1, c2))
  difeq12d(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), wceq(cv(hs0), c0))
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c1)
  csbeq1(s0, cv(hs0), c0, c2)
  csbief(s0, cv(hs0), cdif(c1, c2), cdif(csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2)))
  vex(hs0)
  nfdif(s0, csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2))
  nfcsb1v(s0, cv(hs0), c1)
  nfcsb1v(s0, cv(hs0), c2)
  difeq12d(c1, c2, csb(s0, cv(hs0), c1), csb(s0, cv(hs0), c2), wceq(cv(s0), cv(hs0)))
  csbeq1a(s0, cv(hs0), c1)
  csbeq1a(s0, cv(hs0), c2)
  3eqtr4rd(csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2)), cdif(emptycls, emptycls), emptycls, wn(wcel(c0, universe)))
  a1i(wn(wcel(c0, universe)), wceq(cdif(emptycls, emptycls), emptycls))
  dif0(emptycls)
  difeq12d(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2), emptycls, emptycls, wn(wcel(c0, universe)))
  csbprc(s0, c0, c1)
  csbprc(s0, c0, c2)
  csbprc(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w(wceq(csb(s0, c0, cdif(c1, c2)), cdif(csb(s0, c0, c1), csb(s0, c0, c2))))
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

thm csbdif(setvar s0, class c0, class c1, class c2) {
  ‚ä¢ [c0 / s0](c1 \ c2)=([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2)
} = {
  pm2.61i([c0 / s0](c1 \ c2)=([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2), c0 ‚àà ùïå)
  vtoclg(hs0, c0, universe, [c0 / s0](c1 \ c2)=([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2), [hs0 / s0](c1 \ c2)=([hs0 / s0]c1 \[hs0 / s0]c2))
  eqeq12d([hs0 / s0](c1 \ c2), ([hs0 / s0]c1 \[hs0 / s0]c2), [c0 / s0](c1 \ c2), ([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2), hs0 = c0)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, (c1 \ c2))
  difeq12d([hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2, [c0 / s0]c1, [c0 / s0]c2, hs0 = c0)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, c1)
  csbeq1(s0, hs0, c0, c2)
  csbief(s0, hs0, (c1 \ c2), ([hs0 / s0]c1 \[hs0 / s0]c2))
  vex(hs0)
  nfdif(s0, [hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2)
  nfcsb1v(s0, hs0, c1)
  nfcsb1v(s0, hs0, c2)
  difeq12d(c1, c2, [hs0 / s0]c1, [hs0 / s0]c2, s0 = hs0)
  csbeq1a(s0, hs0, c1)
  csbeq1a(s0, hs0, c2)
  3eqtr4rd([c0 / s0](c1 \ c2), ([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2), (‚àÖ \ ‚àÖ), emptycls, ¬¨ c0 ‚àà ùïå)
  a1i(¬¨ c0 ‚àà ùïå, (‚àÖ \ ‚àÖ)= ‚àÖ)
  dif0(emptycls)
  difeq12d([c0 / s0]c1, [c0 / s0]c2, emptycls, emptycls, ¬¨ c0 ‚àà ùïå)
  csbprc(s0, c0, c1)
  csbprc(s0, c0, c2)
  csbprc(s0, c0, (c1 \ c2))
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.w([c0 / s0](c1 \ c2)=([c0 / s0]c1 \[c0 / s0]c2))
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
}

  syl5eq(csb(s0, c0, cima(ccnv(c2), csn(c4))), cima(ccnv(csb(s0, c0, c2)), csn(csb(s0, c0, c4))), cima(csb(s0, c0, ccnv(c2)), csb(s0, c0, csn(c4))), wcel(c0, c1))
  csbima12(s0, c0, ccnv(c2), csn(c4))
  syl5eqr(cima(csb(s0, c0, ccnv(c2)), csb(s0, c0, csn(c4))), cima(ccnv(csb(s0, c0, c2)), csn(csb(s0, c0, c4))), cima(ccnv(csb(s0, c0, c2)), csb(s0, c0, csn(c4))), wcel(c0, c1))
  imaeq1i(ccnv(csb(s0, c0, c2)), csb(s0, c0, csn(c4)), csb(s0, c0, ccnv(c2)))
  csbcnv(s0, c0, c2)

thm mptsnun(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3) {

blocks.name: topdifinf
blocks.content: Part of Exercise 3 of [Munkres] p. 83. The topology of all subsets ` x ` of ` A ` such that the complement of ` x ` in ` A ` is infinite, or ` x ` is the empty set, or ` x ` is all of ` A ` , is a topology if and only if ` A ` is finite, in which case it is the trivial topology. (Contributed by ML, 17-Jul-2020.)

blocks.name: relowlpssretop
blocks.content: The lower limit topology on the reals is strictly finer than the standard topology. (Contributed by ML, 2-Aug-2020.)

} = {
  impbii(wcel(c0, cxp(c1, c2)), wa(wcel(cfv(c1st, c0), c1), wcel(c0, cxp(universe, c2))))

  ssv(c1)
  ssid(c2)
  xpss12(c1, universe, c2, c2)
  sylanbrc(wa(wcel(cfv(c1st, c0), c1), wcel(c0, cxp(universe, c2))), wcel(c0, cxp(c1, c2)), wcel(c0, cxp(universe, universe)), wa(wcel(cfv(c1st, c0), c1), wcel(cfv(c2nd, c0), c2)))
  adantl(wcel(cfv(c1st, c0), c1), wcel(c0, cxp(universe, c2)), wcel(c0, cxp(universe, universe)))
  sseli(c0, cxp(universe, c2), cxp(universe, universe))
  xpss(universe, c2)

df-finxp
blocks.content: Define Cartesian exponentiation on a class. Note that this definition is limited to finite exponents, since it is defined using nested ordered pairs. If tuples of infinite length are needed, or if they might be needed in the future, use ~ df-ixp or ~ df-map instead. The main advantage of this definition is that it integrates better with functions and relations. For example if ` R ` is a subset of ` ( A ^^ 2o ) ` , then ~ df-br can be used on it, and ~ df-fv can also be used, and so on. It's also worth keeping in mind that ` ( ( U ^^ M ) X. ( U ^^ N ) ) ` is generally not equal to ` ( U ^^ ( M +o N ) ) ` . This definition is technical. Use ~ finxp1o and ~ finxpsuc for a more standard recursive experience. (Contributed by ML, 16-Oct-2020.)
blocks.origin:
axiom df-finxp(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1) {
  |- wceq(cfinxp(c0, c1), cab(s0, wa(wcel(c1, com), wceq(emptycls, cfv(crdg(cmpo(s1, s2, com, universe, cif(emptycls, cif(cop(cuni(cv(s1)), cfv(c1st, cv(s2))), cop(cv(s1), cv(s2)), wcel(cv(s2), cxp(universe, c0))), wa(wceq(cv(s1), c1o), wcel(cv(s2), c0)))), cop(c1, cv(s0))), c1)))))
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s2, c1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
}

  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
} = {
  syl5reqr(emptycls, cfv(cmpo(s0, s1, com, universe, cif(emptycls, cif(cop(cuni(cv(s0)), cfv(c1st, cv(s1))), cop(cv(s0), cv(s1)), wcel(cv(s1), cxp(universe, c1))), wa(wceq(cv(s0), c1o), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))), cop(c1o, c0)), co(c1o, cmpo(s0, s1, com, universe, cif(emptycls, cif(cop(cuni(cv(s0)), cfv(c1st, cv(s1))), cop(cv(s0), cv(s1)), wcel(cv(s1), cxp(universe, c1))), wa(wceq(cv(s0), c1o), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))), c0), wcel(c0, c1))

  anim2d(wcel(c0, c1), wceq(cv(s0), c1o), wceq(cv(s1), c0), wcel(cv(s1), c1))
  eleq1a(c0, c1, cv(s1))
  iftrue(emptycls, cif(cop(cuni(cv(s0)), cfv(c1st, cv(s1))), cop(cv(s0), cv(s1)), wcel(cv(s1), cxp(universe, c1))), wa(wceq(cv(s0), c1o), wcel(cv(s1), c1)))
